"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-volleyball-men-gold-match-results-france-poland-paris-olympics-august-10-2024\", \"text\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors. For context, always refer to the full article.  DOMINATEUR. Gold medalist Jean Patry of France celebrates with fans after ceremony.  Annegret Hilse/Reuters  PARIS, France - France beat the world No. 1-ranked men's volleyball team Poland, 25-19, 25-20, 25-23, to win the Olympic gold on Saturday, August 10, defending its title from the Tokyo Games, but this time on home soil inside a rocking South Paris Arena 1.  France is only the third country to win back-to-back golds in men's volleyball after the former Soviet Union and the United States.  The US beat FIVB world champion Italy instraight setson Friday, August 9, to take the bronze medal.  Jean Patry led the way for the hosts with 17 points and Trevor Clevenot had 11 while Antoine Brizard chipped in with crucial blocks at the net as France claimed a 15th gold medal at its home Games with the sweep victory.  \\\"It's incredible. Right from the start we have been pushed by the fans. The crowd was crazy,\\\" Clevenot said.  \\\"Everyone did well to beat a team like Poland. We will party tonight. We will not finish early!\\\"  Poland, back in the final after 48 years, was left to rue a missed opportunity to claim its second gold.  Poland's biggest star Wilfredo Leon, who had 94 points in Paris, had a quiet game by his standards with just 9 points.  The teams got off to a sizzling start with every spike and block drawing massive roars from a full house.  Poland fell behind in the opening set with several service errors before France wrapped it up when Patry made an excellent dig to set himself up for a devastating kill.  Leon lifted Poland when he attacked with purpose until Brizard denied him a third straight point with the first block of the match, following it up with two more to give France the lead in the second.  Clevenot's clever shot selection for France had been instrumental and he scored three in a row, winning a key battle at the net before sealing a 2-0 lead with a superb spike.  Four monster blocks at the start of the third set the tone for France as things spun out of control for Poland. Sensing a famous win, the home crowd once again got involved in a loud and proud rendition of La Marseillaise - the French anthem.  Poland saved four match points but only delayed the inevitable when Leon's serve went long to spark wild celebrations on the floor and in the stands.  Leon was disappointed with the silver but took pride in standing on the podium.  \\\"We are happy, for a really long time we did not reach the podium at the Olympics,\\\" he said. \\\"So I should be proud of the team.\\\"- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?  follow us          \"}"